1
00:00:01,585 --> 00:00:03,670
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

2
00:01:08,986 --> 00:01:10,487
(PHONE RINGING)

3
00:01:10,571 --> 00:01:13,490
RECEPTIONIST: Good morning,
Adipose Industries.

4
00:01:14,783 --> 00:01:16,410
(DEVICE WHIRRING)

5
00:01:20,330 --> 00:01:22,708
Donna Noble, Health and Safety.

6
00:01:24,876 --> 00:01:27,296
John Smith, Health and Safety.

7
00:01:27,838 --> 00:01:32,968
Adipose Industries,
the 21st century way to lose weight.

8
00:01:33,051 --> 00:01:37,180
No exercise, no diet, no pain,

9
00:01:37,306 --> 00:01:43,103
Just lifelong freedom from fat,
the holy grail of the modern age.

10
00:01:43,186 --> 00:01:45,439
And here it is.

11
00:01:46,189 --> 00:01:51,486
You just take one capsule,
one capsule, once a day for three weeks,

12
00:01:51,612 --> 00:01:53,905
and the fat, as they say...

13
00:01:54,656 --> 00:01:57,284
MALE ANNOUNCER: The fat just walks away.

14
00:01:57,367 --> 00:02:00,370
Excuse me, Miss Foster, if I could?

15
00:02:00,454 --> 00:02:03,957
I'm Penny Carter, science correspondent
for the Observer.

16
00:02:04,041 --> 00:02:06,376
There are a thousand diet pills
on the market,

17
00:02:06,501 --> 00:02:08,712
a thousand con men
stealing people's money.

18
00:02:08,795 --> 00:02:11,506
How do we know the fat isn't going
straight into your bank account?

19
00:02:11,590 --> 00:02:14,217
Oh, Penny, if cynicism
burnt off calories,

20
00:02:14,301 --> 00:02:17,137
we'd all be as thin as rakes.

21
00:02:17,220 --> 00:02:21,183
But if you want the science,
I can oblige.

22
00:02:23,060 --> 00:02:25,228
MALE ANNOUNCER: Adipose Industries.

23
00:02:25,354 --> 00:02:30,275
The Adipose capsule is composed
of a synthesised, mobilising lipase,

24
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:32,944
bound to a large protein molecule.

25
00:02:33,654 --> 00:02:37,240
The mobilising lipase
breaks up the triglycerides

26
00:02:37,366 --> 00:02:40,619
stored in the adipose cells,
which then enter...

27
00:02:40,744 --> 00:02:42,496
Health and Safety.

28
00:02:43,246 --> 00:02:45,082
Film Department.

29
00:02:45,165 --> 00:02:48,919
100% legal, 100% effective.

30
00:02:49,002 --> 00:02:53,256
But can I just ask, how many people
have taken the pills to date?

31
00:02:55,300 --> 00:03:00,597
We've already got 1,000,000 customers
within the Greater London area alone,

32
00:03:00,681 --> 00:03:05,268
but from next week,
we start rolling out nationwide.

33
00:03:05,769 --> 00:03:08,397
The future starts here.

34
00:03:09,272 --> 00:03:13,610
And Britain will be thin.

35
00:03:14,528 --> 00:03:16,029
Good morning,
I represent Adipose Industries.

36
00:03:16,238 --> 00:03:17,781
Good morning,
I represent Adipose Industries.

37
00:03:18,031 --> 00:03:21,076
Good morning,
I represent Adipose Industries...

38
00:03:24,788 --> 00:03:27,999
That's a three-week course of pills
for the special price of £45.

39
00:03:28,125 --> 00:03:31,461
Donna Noble from Health and Safety.
Don't mind me.

40
00:03:34,589 --> 00:03:36,341
We deliver within three working days...

41
00:03:36,425 --> 00:03:38,552
John Smith, Health and Safety.
Don't mind me.

42
00:03:38,635 --> 00:03:42,723
The box comes with 21 days' worth
of pills, a full information pack

43
00:03:42,806 --> 00:03:47,644
and our special free gift,
an Adipose Industries pendant.

44
00:03:47,978 --> 00:03:51,481
It's made of 18 carat gold
and it's yours for free.

45
00:03:52,232 --> 00:03:54,985
No, we don't give away pens. Sorry.

46
00:03:55,068 --> 00:03:57,612
No. I can't make an exception. No.

47
00:03:57,696 --> 00:03:59,614
I'll just need to keep this for testing,

48
00:03:59,698 --> 00:04:01,908
and I just need a list
of your customers.

49
00:04:01,992 --> 00:04:04,536
-Could you print it off?
-I suppose so.

50
00:04:04,661 --> 00:04:07,831
-Where's the printer?
-Just over there, by the plant.

51
00:04:08,165 --> 00:04:09,791
Which plant? That plant?

52
00:04:09,875 --> 00:04:11,460
-Yeah, that's the one.
-Lovely.

53
00:04:11,543 --> 00:04:12,878
That's the printer there?

54
00:04:13,003 --> 00:04:14,713
-By the plant, yeah.
-Brilliant.

55
00:04:14,796 --> 00:04:17,174
Does it need a code? Last place
I worked, the printer needed a code.

56
00:04:17,257 --> 00:04:19,009
No, I can do it from here.

57
00:04:19,134 --> 00:04:21,970
-Has it got paper?
-Yeah, Jimbo keeps it stocked.

58
00:04:22,053 --> 00:04:25,682
Excuse me, everyone,
if I could have your attention...

59
00:04:28,143 --> 00:04:31,980
On average, you're each selling
40 Adipose packs per day.

60
00:04:32,689 --> 00:04:34,232
That's not enough.

61
00:04:34,316 --> 00:04:37,944
I want 100 sales per person per day.

62
00:04:38,028 --> 00:04:40,906
And if not, you'll be replaced.

63
00:04:42,449 --> 00:04:45,619
"Cause If anyone's good at
trimming the fat, it's me.

64
00:04:46,453 --> 00:04:48,997
Now, back to it.

65
00:04:52,626 --> 00:04:54,961
Anyway, if you could
print that off, thanks.

66
00:04:55,045 --> 00:04:58,882
So, if you could just print off
that list, I'll get out of your way.

67
00:04:59,007 --> 00:05:01,218
Lovely. Thanks, then. See you.

68
00:05:01,301 --> 00:05:03,470
Thanks, then. Oh. What's that?

69
00:05:03,553 --> 00:05:05,639
-My telephone number.
-What for?

70
00:05:05,722 --> 00:05:09,059
Health and Safety.
You be Health, I'll be Safety.

71
00:05:09,893 --> 00:05:11,436
Oh, ah...

72
00:05:11,561 --> 00:05:16,066
But that contravenes
paragraph 5, subsection C. Sorry.

73
00:05:26,743 --> 00:05:28,078
Me again.

74
00:05:30,288 --> 00:05:32,207
-Stacy Campbell?
-Who wants to know?

75
00:05:32,332 --> 00:05:36,127
Uh, my name's Donna.
I represent Adipose Industries.

76
00:05:36,211 --> 00:05:39,422
And you're on the list
of our valued customers.

77
00:05:39,756 --> 00:05:43,009
Mr Roger Davey, I'm calling
on behalf of Adipose Industries.

78
00:05:43,093 --> 00:05:44,761
Just need to ask you a few questions.

79
00:05:44,886 --> 00:05:47,722
It's been fantastic.
I started the pills on Thursday.

80
00:05:47,848 --> 00:05:50,642
Five days later, I've lost 11 pounds.

81
00:05:50,767 --> 00:05:54,020
And no side effects or anything?

82
00:05:54,104 --> 00:05:57,315
No, I feel fantastic.
It's a new lease of life.

83
00:05:57,399 --> 00:05:59,651
Now, what do you think about
these earrings? Do they work?

84
00:05:59,776 --> 00:06:01,278
Yeah, lovely.

85
00:06:01,486 --> 00:06:05,448
I've been on the pills two weeks now.
I've lost 14 kilos.

86
00:06:05,532 --> 00:06:08,910
-That's the same amount every day?
-One kilo exactly.

87
00:06:09,035 --> 00:06:11,329
You wake up,
and it's disappeared overnight.

88
00:06:11,454 --> 00:06:15,417
Well, technically speaking,
it's gone by 1:10 in the morning.

89
00:06:16,418 --> 00:06:20,046
-What makes you say that?
-That's when I get woken up.

90
00:06:20,130 --> 00:06:22,757
Might as well weigh myself
at the same time.

91
00:06:22,883 --> 00:06:24,593
You going on a date?

92
00:06:24,676 --> 00:06:29,389
I'm doing the opposite. I'm dumping him.
I can do better than him now.

93
00:06:29,472 --> 00:06:32,809
Right, I won't be long.
If the taxi beeps, give me a shout.

94
00:06:32,934 --> 00:06:34,895
It is driving me mad.

95
00:06:34,978 --> 00:06:40,525
Ten minutes past 1:00, every night,
bang on the dot, without fail,

96
00:06:40,609 --> 00:06:42,819
the burglar alarm goes off.

97
00:06:42,903 --> 00:06:45,030
I've had experts in,
I've had it replaced,

98
00:06:45,155 --> 00:06:46,907
I've even phoned Watchdog.

99
00:06:46,990 --> 00:06:50,327
But no, 1:10 in the morning,
off it goes.

100
00:06:50,410 --> 00:06:53,663
-But with no burglar?
-Nothing. I've given up looking.

101
00:06:53,747 --> 00:06:56,666
Tell me, Roger, have you got a cat flap?

102
00:06:57,500 --> 00:07:00,879
It was here when I bought the house.
I never bothered with it really.

103
00:07:00,962 --> 00:07:02,672
I'm not a cat person.

104
00:07:02,797 --> 00:07:06,343
No, I've met cat people.
You're nothing like them.

105
00:07:06,426 --> 00:07:09,721
Is that what it is, though,
cats getting inside the house?

106
00:07:09,846 --> 00:07:12,140
Well, thing about cat flaps is

107
00:07:12,223 --> 00:07:16,061
they don't just let things in,
they let things out as well.

108
00:07:17,020 --> 00:07:18,605
Like what?

109
00:07:18,688 --> 00:07:21,650
"The fat just walks away."

110
00:07:23,735 --> 00:07:26,780
-Won't be long.
-Oh, that's all right.

111
00:07:41,753 --> 00:07:43,546
(STOMACH GROWLING)

112
00:07:49,052 --> 00:07:50,220
Oh.

113
00:07:53,390 --> 00:07:55,433
(STOMACH GURGLING)

114
00:08:01,147 --> 00:08:02,899
(ALARM SOUNDING)

115
00:08:06,111 --> 00:08:09,072
We have unscheduled parthenogenesis.

116
00:08:09,572 --> 00:08:10,865
Well, thanks for your help.

117
00:08:10,949 --> 00:08:13,868
Tell you what, maybe you could lay off
the pills for a week or so.

118
00:08:13,952 --> 00:08:15,578
(BEEPING)

119
00:08:16,413 --> 00:08:18,123
Gotta go! Sorry!

120
00:08:21,668 --> 00:08:24,838
Send out the collection squad.
Bring them home.

121
00:08:32,929 --> 00:08:34,389
Oh!

122
00:08:40,145 --> 00:08:42,272
You all right out there?

123
00:08:43,690 --> 00:08:44,941
Yeah.

124
00:08:47,402 --> 00:08:49,279
(CREATURE SQUEALING)

125
00:08:49,988 --> 00:08:52,449
The adipose has been witnessed.

126
00:08:52,532 --> 00:08:55,243
FOSTER: Activating full parthenogenesis.

127
00:09:07,464 --> 00:09:08,840
(GURGLING)

128
00:09:14,262 --> 00:09:15,430
What?

129
00:09:16,806 --> 00:09:18,641
(CREATURE SQUEALING)

130
00:09:19,976 --> 00:09:21,478
What are you?

131
00:09:22,645 --> 00:09:24,064
What are you?

132
00:09:24,147 --> 00:09:26,357
I like what you done with the hall.

133
00:09:27,817 --> 00:09:29,027
Stacy?

134
00:09:29,778 --> 00:09:31,154
(GURGLING)

135
00:09:32,030 --> 00:09:33,656
You all right?

136
00:09:36,326 --> 00:09:38,995
Wouldn't mind a little visit myself.

137
00:09:40,997 --> 00:09:43,333
Everything all right in there?

138
00:09:43,958 --> 00:09:45,543
(STACY SOBBING)

139
00:09:47,337 --> 00:09:49,339
It's only me.

140
00:09:49,422 --> 00:09:51,883
Do you mind if I pop to the loo?

141
00:09:52,509 --> 00:09:53,718
Stacy?

142
00:09:57,180 --> 00:09:59,933
Oh, help me! Oh, my God, help me!

143
00:10:00,016 --> 00:10:02,018
What is it? What's wrong?

144
00:10:03,853 --> 00:10:05,355
Stacy!

145
00:10:05,438 --> 00:10:06,856
(SCREAMING)

146
00:10:14,364 --> 00:10:16,157
(POUNDING ON DOOR)

147
00:10:27,293 --> 00:10:28,711
(SQUEAKING)

148
00:11:02,412 --> 00:11:04,247
(CREATURES GURGLING)

149
00:11:04,622 --> 00:11:06,499
(CRASHING)

150
00:11:22,891 --> 00:11:24,642
(CREATURES CRYING)

151
00:11:44,287 --> 00:11:46,039
(DEVICE WHIRRING)

152
00:11:56,132 --> 00:11:58,885
-Stacy Campbell?
-No, she's gone.

153
00:11:58,968 --> 00:12:00,511
Gone where?

154
00:12:00,637 --> 00:12:02,263
She's just gone.

155
00:12:02,347 --> 00:12:04,724
Oh, great. Thanks for nothing.

156
00:12:28,414 --> 00:12:31,918
So, it seems we have a case
of industrial espionage.

157
00:12:32,627 --> 00:12:35,713
One touch and the capsule bio-tunes
itself to its owner,

158
00:12:35,838 --> 00:12:40,760
but someone must have introduced
a second, raw capsule.

159
00:12:40,843 --> 00:12:44,806
Therefore, one of these people
is a thief.

160
00:12:46,516 --> 00:12:47,934
There.

161
00:12:49,018 --> 00:12:50,979
Oh, yes, there she is.

162
00:12:51,688 --> 00:12:52,939
Now...

163
00:12:57,193 --> 00:12:59,404
What should we do with her?

164
00:13:08,371 --> 00:13:11,124
And what time's this?

165
00:13:11,207 --> 00:13:12,709
How old am I?

166
00:13:13,543 --> 00:13:15,878
Not old enough to use a phone.

167
00:13:17,338 --> 00:13:20,008
I thought you were only moving back
for a couple of weeks.

168
00:13:20,091 --> 00:13:21,551
Look at you.

169
00:13:21,676 --> 00:13:24,721
I mean, you're never gonna find a flat,
not while you're on the dole.

170
00:13:24,846 --> 00:13:29,517
It's no good sitting there dressed-up,
looking like you're job-hunting.

171
00:13:29,600 --> 00:13:31,477
You've got to do something.

172
00:13:31,561 --> 00:13:33,354
It's not like the 1980s,

173
00:13:33,438 --> 00:13:36,983
no one's unemployed these days,
except you.

174
00:13:37,066 --> 00:13:39,861
How long did that job
with Health and Safety last?

175
00:13:39,944 --> 00:13:43,573
Two days, and then you walk out.

176
00:13:43,656 --> 00:13:47,285
"I have other plans.”
Well, I've not seen them.

177
00:13:47,744 --> 00:13:50,079
And it's no good sitting there dreaming.

178
00:13:50,204 --> 00:13:52,248
No one's gonna come along
with a magic wand

179
00:13:52,332 --> 00:13:54,584
and make your life all better.

180
00:13:54,667 --> 00:13:58,046
-Where's Granddad?
-Where do you think he is?

181
00:13:58,129 --> 00:14:01,758
Up the hill. He's always up the hill.

182
00:14:07,764 --> 00:14:10,016
Aye, aye, here comes trouble.

183
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:12,435
Permission to board ship, sir.

184
00:14:12,518 --> 00:14:14,354
Permission granted.

185
00:14:14,854 --> 00:14:17,857
-Was she nagging you?
-(LAUGHING) Big time.

186
00:14:18,691 --> 00:14:21,110
-I brought you a Thermos.
-Oh, ta.

187
00:14:21,611 --> 00:14:25,114
-You seen anything?
-Yeah, I've got Venus.

188
00:14:25,239 --> 00:14:29,744
Yeah, with an apparent magnitude
of minus 3.5 at least.

189
00:14:29,827 --> 00:14:34,791
That's what it says in my little book.
Here, have a seat. Come on. Here you go.

190
00:14:35,958 --> 00:14:37,585
You all right?

191
00:14:38,878 --> 00:14:43,383
That's the only planet in
the solar system named after a woman.

192
00:14:45,218 --> 00:14:46,761
Good for her.

193
00:14:47,970 --> 00:14:49,472
How far away is that?

194
00:14:49,597 --> 00:14:53,059
Oh, it's about 26,000,000 miles.

195
00:14:53,768 --> 00:14:56,312
But we'll get there one day.

196
00:14:57,146 --> 00:15:01,484
100 years' time, we'll be
striding out amongst the stars,

197
00:15:01,567 --> 00:15:05,071
jiggling about with all them aliens,
just you wait.

198
00:15:06,656 --> 00:15:09,242
You really believe in all that stuff,
don't you?

199
00:15:09,325 --> 00:15:12,453
Oh, they're all over the place
these days.

200
00:15:12,537 --> 00:15:14,330
If I wait here long enough...

201
00:15:14,414 --> 00:15:17,583
I don't suppose you've seen
a little blue box.

202
00:15:18,126 --> 00:15:19,877
Is that slang for something?

203
00:15:20,002 --> 00:15:22,588
No, I mean it.

204
00:15:23,548 --> 00:15:27,927
If you ever see a little blue box
flying up there in the sky,

205
00:15:28,010 --> 00:15:30,471
you shout for me, Gramps.

206
00:15:30,555 --> 00:15:32,640
Oh, you just shout.

207
00:15:36,018 --> 00:15:40,189
Do you know, I don't understand
half the things you say these days.

208
00:15:40,273 --> 00:15:42,859
-Nor me.
-No, fair dues.

209
00:15:43,943 --> 00:15:46,821
You've had a funny old time
of it lately.

210
00:15:46,904 --> 00:15:50,199
There was poor old whatshisname,
Lance, bless him.

211
00:15:51,033 --> 00:15:53,202
That barmy old Christmas.

212
00:15:55,037 --> 00:15:57,707
I wish you'd tell us
what really happened.

213
00:15:57,790 --> 00:15:59,041
I know.

214
00:15:59,792 --> 00:16:01,377
It's just...

215
00:16:02,628 --> 00:16:06,424
The things I've seen,
sometimes I think I'm going mad.

216
00:16:06,507 --> 00:16:09,135
I mean, even tonight, I was in a...

217
00:16:12,054 --> 00:16:13,973
Doesn't matter.

218
00:16:14,056 --> 00:16:17,185
Well, you're not yourself,
I'll give you that.

219
00:16:17,268 --> 00:16:20,646
You just...
You seem to be drifting, sweetheart.

220
00:16:20,730 --> 00:16:22,607
I'm not drifting.

221
00:16:24,066 --> 00:16:26,736
-I'm waiting.
-What for?

222
00:16:27,695 --> 00:16:29,572
The right man.

223
00:16:29,655 --> 00:16:31,616
(LAUGHING)

224
00:16:31,741 --> 00:16:33,701
Same old story! A man!

225
00:16:34,994 --> 00:16:37,246
Oh, I don't mean like that.

226
00:16:38,164 --> 00:16:40,958
But he's real. I've seen him.

227
00:16:41,042 --> 00:16:43,127
I've met him, just once.

228
00:16:43,794 --> 00:16:46,923
And then I let him fly away.

229
00:16:47,757 --> 00:16:51,093
-Well, there you are. Go and find him.
-I've tried.

230
00:16:51,761 --> 00:16:53,930
He's nowhere.

231
00:16:54,055 --> 00:16:56,557
Hey, not like you to give up.

232
00:16:57,808 --> 00:17:00,436
You know, I remember
when you was about six years old,

233
00:17:00,520 --> 00:17:03,105
your mother said,
"No holiday this year."

234
00:17:03,231 --> 00:17:08,069
So off you toddled all on your own
and you got on a bus to Strathclyde.

235
00:17:08,152 --> 00:17:11,572
Hah! We had the police out
and everything.

236
00:17:11,656 --> 00:17:14,575
Hah! Where's she gone, then?

237
00:17:15,618 --> 00:17:17,912
Where's that girl, eh?

238
00:17:18,621 --> 00:17:20,122
You're right.

239
00:17:21,582 --> 00:17:24,544
'Cause he's still out there, somewhere.

240
00:17:26,003 --> 00:17:28,172
And I'll find him, Gramps,

241
00:17:29,298 --> 00:17:31,801
even if I have to wait 100 years.

242
00:17:33,094 --> 00:17:34,679
I'll find him.

243
00:17:39,559 --> 00:17:41,310
Oh, fascinating.

244
00:17:42,270 --> 00:17:46,023
Seems to be a bio-flip digital stitch
specifically for...

245
00:18:06,711 --> 00:18:10,089
It's my turn for the car.
What do you need it for?

246
00:18:11,048 --> 00:18:12,758
A quick getaway.

247
00:18:29,775 --> 00:18:31,569
(WHOOSHING)

248
00:18:55,009 --> 00:18:56,385
Morning.

249
00:19:20,493 --> 00:19:23,079
Keep an eye out. She'll come back.

250
00:19:23,537 --> 00:19:26,749
And then she's mine.

251
00:19:36,842 --> 00:19:38,969
-See you tomorrow.
-Night.

252
00:19:57,113 --> 00:19:58,781
(MOBILE RINGING)

253
00:20:02,618 --> 00:20:04,078
(WHISPERING) Not now.

254
00:20:04,161 --> 00:20:06,872
I need the car. Where are you?

255
00:20:07,123 --> 00:20:08,958
I can't. I'm busy.

256
00:20:09,041 --> 00:20:10,626
Why are you whispering?

257
00:20:10,710 --> 00:20:12,378
I'm in church.

258
00:20:12,461 --> 00:20:14,797
What are you doing in church?

259
00:20:15,464 --> 00:20:18,384
-Praying.
-Ha! Bit late for that, madam.

260
00:20:18,467 --> 00:20:20,219
What's she in church for?

261
00:20:20,302 --> 00:20:22,471
Hush, you. Go up the hill.

262
00:20:24,140 --> 00:20:27,101
But I need the car.
I'm going out with Suzette.

263
00:20:27,184 --> 00:20:28,686
She's asked all the Wednesday girls.

264
00:20:28,769 --> 00:20:31,230
Apparently, she's been on
those Adipose pills.

265
00:20:31,313 --> 00:20:32,940
She says she looks marvellous.

266
00:20:33,023 --> 00:20:34,859
(CRASHING)

267
00:20:38,612 --> 00:20:40,156
We know you're in here,

268
00:20:40,239 --> 00:20:44,076
so why don't you make this nice and easy
and show yourself?

269
00:20:46,620 --> 00:20:48,164
I'm waiting.

270
00:20:49,331 --> 00:20:53,002
I warn you, I'm not a patient woman.
Now, out you come.

271
00:20:54,211 --> 00:20:55,421
Right.

272
00:20:56,422 --> 00:20:58,549
We'll do it the hard way.

273
00:20:59,341 --> 00:21:00,801
Get her.

274
00:21:12,146 --> 00:21:13,731
There you are.

275
00:21:15,900 --> 00:21:20,112
I've been through the records, Foster,
and all of your results have been faked.

276
00:21:20,196 --> 00:21:22,323
There's something about those pills
you're not telling us.

277
00:21:22,406 --> 00:21:25,951
Oh, I think I'll be conducting
this interview, Penny.

278
00:21:52,853 --> 00:21:55,606
You've got no right to do this.
Let me go.

279
00:22:11,497 --> 00:22:13,332
This is ridiculous.

280
00:22:16,919 --> 00:22:18,546
Sit there.

281
00:22:18,629 --> 00:22:21,298
-I'm phoning my editor.
-I said, sit.

282
00:22:23,300 --> 00:22:24,969
PENNY: You can't tie me up.

283
00:22:25,094 --> 00:22:26,846
What sort of a country
do you think this is?

284
00:22:26,929 --> 00:22:30,099
Oh, it's a beautifully fat country.

285
00:22:30,182 --> 00:22:33,686
And believe me, I've travelled a long
way to find obesity on this scale.

286
00:22:33,769 --> 00:22:35,855
So, come on then, Miss Foster,

287
00:22:35,938 --> 00:22:38,649
those pills, what are they?

288
00:22:39,441 --> 00:22:44,029
Well, you might as well have a scoop,
since you'll never see it printed.

289
00:22:44,405 --> 00:22:48,826
This is the spark of life.

290
00:22:49,869 --> 00:22:51,787
And what's that supposed to mean?

291
00:22:51,871 --> 00:22:56,417
Officially, the capsule attracts all
the fat cells and flushes them away.

292
00:22:56,500 --> 00:22:59,920
Well, it certainly attracts them,
that part's true.

293
00:23:00,004 --> 00:23:03,757
But it binds the fat together
and galvanises it to form a body.

294
00:23:03,841 --> 00:23:06,218
What do you mean, a body?

295
00:23:06,302 --> 00:23:08,721
I am surprised you never
asked about my name.

296
00:23:08,804 --> 00:23:10,514
I chose it well.

297
00:23:12,266 --> 00:23:13,893
Foster.

298
00:23:13,976 --> 00:23:15,936
As in "foster mother".

299
00:23:17,938 --> 00:23:19,773
And these

300
00:23:22,943 --> 00:23:24,194
are my children.

301
00:23:24,320 --> 00:23:28,449
PENNY: Are you kidding me? I don't...
What the hell is that?

302
00:23:28,532 --> 00:23:30,200
Adipose.

303
00:23:32,328 --> 00:23:36,373
It's called an adipose,

304
00:23:37,291 --> 00:23:39,668
made out of living fat.

305
00:23:40,961 --> 00:23:44,882
PENNY: I don't understand.
FOSTER: From ordinary human people.

306
00:23:51,138 --> 00:23:52,973
(MOUTHS)

307
00:24:56,829 --> 00:24:59,206
Are we interrupting you?

308
00:25:01,667 --> 00:25:03,252
Get her!

309
00:25:05,087 --> 00:25:06,547
And him!

310
00:25:33,615 --> 00:25:35,325
What about me?

311
00:25:43,751 --> 00:25:45,711
Oh, my God!

312
00:25:45,794 --> 00:25:47,504
I don't believe it!

313
00:25:47,629 --> 00:25:50,049
You've even got the same suit!

314
00:25:50,132 --> 00:25:53,761
-Don't you ever change?
-Yeah, thanks, Donna, not right now.

315
00:25:58,724 --> 00:26:00,642
Just like old times.

316
00:26:03,520 --> 00:26:05,564
DONNA: 'Cause I thought,
"How do you find the Doctor?"

317
00:26:05,689 --> 00:26:08,275
And then I just thought, "Look for
trouble, and then he'll turn up.”

318
00:26:08,358 --> 00:26:10,277
So I looked everywhere, you name it.

319
00:26:10,360 --> 00:26:13,447
UFO sightings, crop circles,
sea monsters.

320
00:26:13,530 --> 00:26:15,157
I looked, I found them all.

321
00:26:15,282 --> 00:26:18,702
That song about the bees disappearing,
I thought, "I bet he's connected.”

322
00:26:18,786 --> 00:26:21,997
'Cause the thing is, Doctor,
I believe it all now.

323
00:26:22,081 --> 00:26:25,292
You opened my eyes to all those
amazing things out there.

324
00:26:25,375 --> 00:26:28,337
I believe them all. Well, apart
from that replica of the 7itanic

325
00:26:28,420 --> 00:26:29,963
flying over Buckingham Palace
on Christmas Day.

326
00:26:30,047 --> 00:26:31,340
That's got to be a hoax!

327
00:26:31,465 --> 00:26:33,217
What do you mean,
the bees are disappearing?

328
00:26:33,342 --> 00:26:35,427
I don't know. That's what it says
on the Internet.

329
00:26:35,511 --> 00:26:37,679
On the same site, there was
all these conspiracy theories

330
00:26:37,805 --> 00:26:39,848
about Adipose Industries,
and I thought, "Let's take a look."

331
00:26:39,932 --> 00:26:41,850
-In you get!
-What, in that thing?

332
00:26:41,934 --> 00:26:43,352
Yes, "in that thing".

333
00:26:43,435 --> 00:26:45,604
But if we go down in that,
they'll just call us back up again.

334
00:26:45,687 --> 00:26:47,523
No, no, I locked the controls
with a sonic cage.

335
00:26:47,648 --> 00:26:49,191
I'm the only one that can control it.

336
00:26:49,274 --> 00:26:51,693
Not unless she's got a sonic device
of her own, which is very unlikely.

337
00:26:53,028 --> 00:26:55,030
Out of my way.

338
00:27:15,217 --> 00:27:16,635
FOSTER: Oh.

339
00:27:16,718 --> 00:27:18,554
Oh, I don't think so.

340
00:27:22,683 --> 00:27:24,601
(BOTH YELLING)

341
00:27:40,701 --> 00:27:43,662
Hold on! Hold on, we can go in
through the window.

342
00:27:43,745 --> 00:27:45,789
Deadlock the building.

343
00:27:45,914 --> 00:27:47,875
I can't get it open!

344
00:27:49,960 --> 00:27:51,753
Smash it, then!

345
00:28:07,227 --> 00:28:09,479
She's cutting the cable!

346
00:28:12,316 --> 00:28:13,859
(DONNA SCREAMING)

347
00:28:13,942 --> 00:28:15,527
Donna!

348
00:28:16,653 --> 00:28:18,113
Doctor!

349
00:28:18,906 --> 00:28:20,365
Hold on!

350
00:28:20,449 --> 00:28:22,034
I am!

351
00:28:30,459 --> 00:28:31,585
Doctor!

352
00:28:35,881 --> 00:28:37,799
FOSTER: And now for the other one.

353
00:29:10,457 --> 00:29:12,251
I'm gonna fall!

354
00:29:16,213 --> 00:29:17,839
What the hell is going on?

355
00:29:19,424 --> 00:29:21,802
This is all your fault.

356
00:29:21,885 --> 00:29:23,845
I should have stayed at home.

357
00:29:24,179 --> 00:29:26,098
I won't be a minute.

358
00:29:32,896 --> 00:29:34,940
Yes, he's slippery, that one.

359
00:29:35,065 --> 00:29:37,317
Time we found out who he is.

360
00:29:50,706 --> 00:29:52,791
Is anyone going to tell me
what's going on?

361
00:29:52,874 --> 00:29:55,127
-What are you, a journalist?
-Yes.

362
00:29:55,210 --> 00:29:57,045
Well, make it up!

363
00:29:57,254 --> 00:29:58,422
Get off!

364
00:29:59,214 --> 00:30:02,384
I've got you, I've got you.
Donna, stop kicking!

365
00:30:09,349 --> 00:30:11,977
I was right. It's always like this
with you, isn't it?

366
00:30:12,060 --> 00:30:13,895
Oh, yes. And off we go!

367
00:30:15,230 --> 00:30:16,440
Oi!

368
00:30:17,399 --> 00:30:18,817
Sorry.

369
00:30:20,861 --> 00:30:23,238
Now do yourself a favour. Get out!

370
00:30:28,827 --> 00:30:30,579
FOSTER: Well, then.

371
00:30:32,289 --> 00:30:33,749
At last.

372
00:30:33,832 --> 00:30:34,875
Hello.

373
00:30:34,958 --> 00:30:37,753
-Nice to meet you. I'm the Doctor.
-And I'm Donna.

374
00:30:37,878 --> 00:30:39,921
Partners in crime.

375
00:30:40,005 --> 00:30:43,842
And evidently off-worlders,
judging by your sonic technology.

376
00:30:44,760 --> 00:30:48,055
Oh, yes. I've still got your sonic pen.

377
00:30:48,138 --> 00:30:49,848
Nice. I like it. Sleek.

378
00:30:49,931 --> 00:30:52,517
-It's kind of sleek.
-Oh, it's definitely sleek.

379
00:30:52,601 --> 00:30:56,104
And if you were to sign your real name,
that would be...?

380
00:30:56,521 --> 00:31:00,108
Matron Cofelia of the Five-Straighten
Classabindi Nursery Fleet.

381
00:31:00,192 --> 00:31:02,069
Intergalactic class.

382
00:31:02,194 --> 00:31:04,071
A wet nurse.

383
00:31:04,154 --> 00:31:06,782
Using humans as surrogates.

384
00:31:06,865 --> 00:31:09,284
I've been employed
by the Adiposian First Family

385
00:31:09,368 --> 00:31:13,121
to foster a new generation
after their breeding planet was lost.

386
00:31:13,288 --> 00:31:15,415
What do you mean, lost?
How do you lose a planet?

387
00:31:15,499 --> 00:31:17,459
Oh, the politics are none of my concern.

388
00:31:17,542 --> 00:31:21,213
I'm just here to take care of
the children on behalf of the parents.

389
00:31:21,296 --> 00:31:23,673
What, like an outer space super-nanny?

390
00:31:23,799 --> 00:31:26,009
Yes, if you like.

391
00:31:26,134 --> 00:31:27,594
So...

392
00:31:27,677 --> 00:31:31,348
So those little things,
they're made out of fat, yeah?

393
00:31:31,431 --> 00:31:34,684
But that woman, Stacy Campbell,
there was nothing left of her.

394
00:31:34,810 --> 00:31:39,815
Oh, in a crisis, the adipose can convert
bone and hair and internal organs.

395
00:31:39,940 --> 00:31:42,609
It makes them
a little bit sick, poor things.

396
00:31:43,610 --> 00:31:45,404
What about poor Stacy?

397
00:31:46,029 --> 00:31:49,241
Seeding a level five planet
is against galactic law.

398
00:31:51,326 --> 00:31:53,787
Are you threatening me?

399
00:31:53,870 --> 00:31:56,415
I'm trying to help you, Matron.

400
00:31:56,498 --> 00:31:58,959
This is your one chance.

401
00:31:59,042 --> 00:32:02,671
'Cause if you don't call this off,
then I'll have to stop you.

402
00:32:04,005 --> 00:32:06,174
I hardly think you can stop bullets.

403
00:32:06,716 --> 00:32:10,429
No, hold on, hold on, hold on!
One more thing, before dying.

404
00:32:10,512 --> 00:32:12,055
Do you know what happens

405
00:32:12,139 --> 00:32:15,851
if you hold two identical sonic devices
against each other?

406
00:32:16,977 --> 00:32:18,061
No.

407
00:32:18,186 --> 00:32:20,147
Nor me. Let's find out.

408
00:32:27,279 --> 00:32:28,697
Come on!

409
00:32:32,200 --> 00:32:35,871
I'm advancing the birth plan.
We're going into premature lab our.

410
00:32:38,373 --> 00:32:40,459
Cellular basification.

411
00:32:43,044 --> 00:32:44,379
Tie her up.

412
00:32:45,422 --> 00:32:47,048
Oh, you're kidding me.

413
00:32:57,100 --> 00:33:00,896
Well, that's one solution,
hiding in a cupboard.

414
00:33:00,979 --> 00:33:02,647
I like it.

415
00:33:02,731 --> 00:33:05,609
Been hacking into this thing all day
"cause the Matron's got a computer core

416
00:33:05,692 --> 00:33:08,612
running through the centre
of the building. Triple-deadlocked.

417
00:33:08,737 --> 00:33:11,907
But now I've got this,
I can get into it.

418
00:33:17,704 --> 00:33:19,664
What does that thing do?

419
00:33:19,748 --> 00:33:21,416
It's the inducer.

420
00:33:22,417 --> 00:33:24,252
We had planned to seed millions,

421
00:33:25,420 --> 00:33:28,673
but if that man's an alien, then
he's alerted the Shadow Proclamation.

422
00:33:28,757 --> 00:33:31,843
So the first 1,000,000 humans
will have to do.

423
00:33:31,927 --> 00:33:33,428
Find him.

424
00:33:33,512 --> 00:33:36,389
And the woman.
Don't waste time, just kill them.

425
00:33:38,892 --> 00:33:40,602
She's wired up the whole building.

426
00:33:42,604 --> 00:33:44,773
We need a bit of privacy.

427
00:33:45,482 --> 00:33:47,692
(GUARDS SCREAMING)

428
00:33:48,276 --> 00:33:50,111
Just enough to stop them.

429
00:33:50,195 --> 00:33:52,948
Why has she wired up a tower block?

430
00:33:53,031 --> 00:33:54,783
What's it all for?

431
00:34:02,791 --> 00:34:04,960
COMPUTER: Inducer online.

432
00:34:08,797 --> 00:34:10,298
You look older.

433
00:34:10,382 --> 00:34:11,800
Thanks.

434
00:34:12,467 --> 00:34:14,678
-Still on your own?
-Yeah.

435
00:34:15,345 --> 00:34:19,140
Well, no. I had this friend.
Martha she was called.

436
00:34:19,266 --> 00:34:22,060
Martha Jones. She was brilliant.

437
00:34:22,143 --> 00:34:24,479
And I destroyed half her life.

438
00:34:25,981 --> 00:34:28,149
But she's fine, she's good.

439
00:34:28,984 --> 00:34:30,652
She's gone.

440
00:34:31,695 --> 00:34:33,572
What about Rose?

441
00:34:34,573 --> 00:34:36,449
Still lost.

442
00:34:37,617 --> 00:34:40,662
I thought you were going to
travel the world.

443
00:34:40,745 --> 00:34:42,664
Easier said than done.

444
00:34:43,456 --> 00:34:47,002
It's like I had that one day with you,
and I was going to change.

445
00:34:47,085 --> 00:34:49,296
I was going to do so much.

446
00:34:50,380 --> 00:34:52,632
Then I woke up the next morning...

447
00:34:52,716 --> 00:34:54,426
Same old life.

448
00:34:56,011 --> 00:34:58,346
It's like you were never there.

449
00:34:59,514 --> 00:35:02,434
And I tried...I did try.

450
00:35:03,226 --> 00:35:07,147
I went to Egypt. I was going to go
barefoot and everything.

451
00:35:07,981 --> 00:35:10,233
And then it's all bus trips
and guidebooks

452
00:35:10,317 --> 00:35:13,695
and "Don't drink the water"
and two weeks later you're back home.

453
00:35:15,322 --> 00:35:17,616
It's nothing like being with you.

454
00:35:18,450 --> 00:35:20,493
I must have been mad
turning down that offer.

455
00:35:20,577 --> 00:35:22,621
What offer?

456
00:35:22,704 --> 00:35:24,539
To come with you.

457
00:35:25,540 --> 00:35:27,584
Come with me?

458
00:35:27,667 --> 00:35:29,169
Oh, yes, please!

459
00:35:31,171 --> 00:35:32,297
Right.

460
00:35:32,380 --> 00:35:34,424
COMPUTER: Inducer activated.

461
00:35:34,633 --> 00:35:37,177
-What's it doing now?
-She's started the programme.

462
00:35:38,720 --> 00:35:40,805
COMPUTER: Inducer transmitting.

463
00:35:41,598 --> 00:35:43,600
Mark the date, Miss Carter.

464
00:35:44,434 --> 00:35:46,227
Happy birthday.

465
00:35:47,729 --> 00:35:51,816
1,000,000 birthdays.

466
00:35:55,570 --> 00:35:58,406
I swear, that Adipose treatment
is fabulous.

467
00:35:58,490 --> 00:36:00,367
Just look at my chin.

468
00:36:00,950 --> 00:36:04,037
And it's very good for back fat.
I'm down two sizes.

469
00:36:04,120 --> 00:36:08,083
It's like a miracle.
All that from just one little pill.

470
00:36:08,208 --> 00:36:10,418
And I've been eating like normal...

471
00:36:11,753 --> 00:36:12,921
(GURGLING)

472
00:36:13,004 --> 00:36:15,173
-You all right, love?
-Yeah, I'm...

473
00:36:16,132 --> 00:36:17,926
Just...

474
00:36:18,510 --> 00:36:21,596
Funny sort of feeling, like something...

475
00:36:22,222 --> 00:36:24,307
I'm not sure, it just seems to be...

476
00:36:24,933 --> 00:36:27,268
Better pop to the loo.

477
00:36:28,937 --> 00:36:31,106
-Oh, my God! Suzette...
-What?

478
00:36:36,277 --> 00:36:38,071
What is it?

479
00:36:38,154 --> 00:36:39,614
Get it off me!

480
00:36:49,666 --> 00:36:51,334
(SQUEALS PLAYFULLY)

481
00:37:24,617 --> 00:37:26,911
(SQUEALING)

482
00:37:48,933 --> 00:37:50,977
Come to me, children.

483
00:37:51,811 --> 00:37:53,229
Come to me.

484
00:37:54,105 --> 00:37:56,816
WOMAN: Get back. Everyone get back.
Don't touch them.

485
00:37:56,900 --> 00:37:59,319
-Keep away...
-Just leave them.

486
00:38:08,536 --> 00:38:09,788
So far they're just losing weight,

487
00:38:09,871 --> 00:38:12,123
but the Matron's gone up
to emergency parthenogenesis.

488
00:38:12,207 --> 00:38:15,043
-And that's when they convert...
-Skeletons, organs, everything.

489
00:38:15,126 --> 00:38:16,836
1,000,000 people are going to die.

490
00:38:26,554 --> 00:38:28,473
I've got to cancel the signal.

491
00:38:29,265 --> 00:38:30,892
This contains the primary signal.

492
00:38:30,975 --> 00:38:34,145
If I can switch it off, the fat
goes back to being just fat.

493
00:38:34,479 --> 00:38:36,439
Oh, nice try.

494
00:38:36,523 --> 00:38:38,149
Double strength.

495
00:38:38,858 --> 00:38:41,069
COMPUTER: Inducer increasing.

496
00:38:41,152 --> 00:38:44,280
No, no, no! She's doubled it! I need...

497
00:38:44,405 --> 00:38:47,575
I haven't got time.
It's too far. I can't override it.

498
00:38:47,659 --> 00:38:49,118
They're all going to die.

499
00:38:53,581 --> 00:38:56,918
-Is there anything I can do?
-Sorry, Donna, this is way beyond you.

500
00:38:57,001 --> 00:38:58,795
I've got to double the base pulse.
I can't...

501
00:38:58,920 --> 00:39:01,172
Doctor, tell me, what do you need?

502
00:39:01,256 --> 00:39:03,216
I need a second capsule
to boost the override,

503
00:39:03,299 --> 00:39:05,426
but I've only got the one.
I can't save them.

504
